manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Frequently Asked Questions Q: Does this phone come with a SIM Card or do I need to purchase an additional SIM Card to Activate? A: This phone does come with a SIM Card that is ready to activate. You do not need to buy a separate SIM card. Q: Where can I buy a service plan or airtime for this phone? A: Service plans and airtime cards are available at Amazon.com. Q: How do I activate service on my new device? A: You can activate on the Tracfone website. Have your new phone’s IMEI/MEID/Serial # and a service plan PIN ready and follow the step-by-step instructions on the red card that comes with your device. Q: Is this phone unlocked? A: No, this phone is locked to the Tracfone network and can only be activated with a compatible Tracfone service plan. Q: Can I use this phone outside of the US? A: This phone cannot be used outside of the United States unless you are using a Tracfone Wireless plan that includes international roaming.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 18, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Great Phone that's worth 3x the asking price.Setup is easy and seamless.Lots of storage space with great call quality.Audio from speaker is decent and camera gets the job done.Battery can easily power phone for 24+ hrs depending on usage.Overall, extremely happy with my purchase

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars great phone for the price!
reviews.reviewText: This phone has quick performance and a nice display. It's not a 1000 dollar phone but sure feels like it. The camera and display aren't that of a 1000 dollar phone but they are better than most phones at this price. If you want a phone with 2023 features and performance for under 200 This phone is perfect for you. The only downside is there was no USB charging block included but that is just the norm these days , so if you want a fast 20w charger you have to buy it separately.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Great phone for value. I am not a big user, and this phone is ideal and does everything I need. Easy to transfer files from old Tracfone. It is a Samsung product which is very good. I do not need an expensive iphone.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This phone is so much fun. Has a lot of storage,takes crystal clear pictures,has good sounds,and ringtones.it also stays charge for like 2 days and I go on it a lot. The only thing I don't like is when I do have to charge it,it takes a long time. My old phone use to charge fast. But this is my favorite phone out of all the phones I've had. I highly recommend

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Previously I have always been satisfied with Samsung phones. I had 2 prior to this purchase(models J3 and A10e) This phone is larger and heavier. Uncomfortable to carry in shirt pocket. It also was unable to send or receive pictures within text messages. I did some research and I am not the only one that has had the texting problem. I was able to return the phone to Amazon for a refund. Do yourself a favor don't buy this model.

Reviewed in the United States on December 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great phone, but still has lots of bloatware.
reviews.reviewText: I bought 2 to replace our galaxy A51's. Probably easy to operate because these are our 3rd galaxy phones. The camera & video recorder are superlative. To me it's worth it just for that. There are many more good features, but yeah, there is the bloatware. Over 400 apps are pre-installed. 2 things about that. 1. There are other apps superior to some of Samsung's I prefer & that I'm used to. 2. You can't get rid of the ones you don't like/won't use. That raises another problem because the A14 has only half the storage capacity of the A51. At the same time it irritates me that it's forever trying to put my non Samsung apps into deep sleep. It's crucial that some of them stay enabled. I play zero games, but whenever sam updates my phone they like to throw a couple in. Most of them are system apps otherwise.It threw me off to see it required a USBC to USBC cable and the special charging block didn't come with it. Fortunately my brother had an extra.
